# React Standards

## Components

- **Functional components only**; no class components.
- **Colocate** component + hook + styles in the same feature folder when possible.
- Split **container** (data/subscriptions) from **presentational** (pure UI) for panels and HUD.

## Next.js App Router

- **R3F / Canvas** must load via `next/dynamic` with `{ ssr: false }`.
- **3D content is client-only** — never render `<Canvas>` in Server Components.
- Page shell (layout, metadata, providers) in App Router; world runtime in client components.
- MVP entry: `/world/megacity`; dynamic `[scale]` routes as fallback.

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS** for all 2D UI; use `GlassPanel` and design tokens from `docs/design-system/`.
- No CSS-in-JS (styled-components, Emotion) — conflicts with R3F and SSR strategy.
- Fonts via `next/font`: Orbitron (headings), Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code).

## Hooks

- Extract reusable logic into **`use*`** hooks in `apps/web/hooks/`.
- Cross-store coordination via composite hooks (e.g., `useSelectEntity`) — not inline store coupling.
- Subscribe with **narrow selectors**: `useWorldStore(s => s.entities[id])`, not whole-store subscriptions.

## Performance

- **`memo`** on heavy HUD/panel components that receive stable props.
- **`useCallback` / `useMemo`** only when profiling shows benefit — not by default.
- List keys must be **stable entity IDs**, never array index for dynamic world data.

## Accessibility

- Every interactive 3D action needs a **2D alternative** (keyboard nav, search, panel controls).
- HUD controls: proper `aria-*`, focus management in dialogue panels.
